text: Michael L Payne (born 1941), is a male former swimmer who competed for England. ==Swimming career== He represented England in the 110 yards backstroke at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games in Cardiff, Wales. He swam for the Bristol Central Club. ==References== Category:1941 births Category:English male swimmers Category:Swimmers at the 1958 British Empire and Commonwealth Games Category:Living people
